      "description": "Offered is an uncompromising 2004 BMW M3, a pinnacle of analog performance. At its heart lies the S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS timing for a razor-sharp throttle response and an 8,000 RPM redline. Power is delivered through a precise six-speed Getrag manual transmission to a variable M-Differential lock, ensuring optimal power distribution during high-lateral-G cornering. This example maintains factory-spec chassis rigidity with no subframe fatigue. The suspension geometry remains true, providing the communicative feedback and neutral balance the E46 chassis is legendary for. Every mechanical component, from the cross-drilled rotors to the bushings, reflects a vehicle preserved in showroom-fresh state.",
